    <p>Complete HVAC system replacement in Spokane typically ranges from \$8,000-15,000 for a standard 2,000 square foot home. Heat pump systems average \$7,200-12,000 installed, while traditional AC units with gas furnaces range \$6,500-11,000. Ductless mini-split systems cost \$3,000-8,000 depending on the number of zones. Higher-end variable-speed systems or homes requiring extensive ductwork can reach \$18,000-25,000. At Spokane's 9.8¬¢/kWh electricity rate, efficient heat pumps typically provide the best long-term value due to reduced heating costs during the extended winter season.</p>
