  </div>
  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">How do I choose a contractor in Spokane?</h3>
    <p>Choose contractors with current Washington mechanical contractor licenses, strong local references, and proven cold-climate expertise. Verify Better Business Bureau ratings, check recent Google reviews, and request references from installations completed within the past year. Quality contractors provide detailed load calculations, explain system options clearly, offer comprehensive warranties (5-10 years equipment, 1-2 years labor), and provide 24/7 emergency service during winter months. Ensure they're knowledgeable about Avista rebate programs and can handle the paperwork to maximize your savings. Get written estimates from at least three licensed contractors before making your decision.</p>
